    ```javascript
function minOperations(nums, target) {
    const n = nums.length;
    const sum_nums = nums.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0);
    const sum_target = target.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0);
    const diff = (sum_target - sum_nums) / 2;
    let cnt = 0;
    for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (nums[i] > target[i]) {
            cnt += (nums[i] - target[i] - diff) / 2;
        }
    }
    return cnt;
}
```


    1. Calculate the sum of both nums and target arrays.
2. Calculate the difference in sum (sum_target - sum_nums) and divide by 2.
3. For each element in nums, if it's greater than the corresponding element in target, increment the count cnt by the difference between the elements, minus diff and then divide by 2.
4. Return the cnt as the minimum number of operations required to make nums similar to target.

